Current remake systems already implemented:

- Basic React/Electron app shell
- Generated static data loaded from `src/data/generated`
- Original-style public assets copied under `public/game-assets`
- Basic customer list
- Generated NPC inventories
- Player inventory
- Player/NPC offer panels
- Basic move controls: click, right click, shift, alt
- Protect/star action
- Search/sort inventory panels
- Basic offer valuation and accept/refuse trade
- Character/profession/market bias in valuation
- Simple route list/map display
- Day advancement on travel
- Read-only market quest/event notes
- Local save/load/import/export
- Basic mod pack override support
- Basic audio routing

Do not reopen the original bundle for these already-known facts. Reopen it only when extracting more structured source data that is not already in `src/data/generated`, such as full dialogue graphs, callback ids, text/image item payloads, or exact original minigame rules.

